<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-722-911  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 722 911.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  Dec 17 1990 v4 n41 p12(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>AF's JUSTIS in limbo, waits for CIM adoption. (Air Force's JointUniform Services Technical Information System, DefenseDepartment's Corporate Information Management)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Marsan, Carolyn Duffy.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Air Force technical manual information system, called theJoint Uniform Services Technical Information System, or JUSTIS,awaits approval and funding as part of the Department of Defense'sCorporate Information Management (CIM) program.andP;  JUSTIS officialsplan to brief CIM planners on the system's status in Jan 1991 andhope that JUSTIS will be an official CIM program by Mar 1991.andO;They are working with the Office of the Secretary of Defense todetermine how JUSTIS fits into the CIM process model.andP;  The CIMinitiative is to develop standard information systems in materialsmanagement, contract payments, payroll and similar areas.andP;  Other,approved CIM systems had already been developed when they wereselected as interim solutions; JUSTIS is the first new systembeing developed from scratch.andP;  The Air Force is currently payingfor the program office, which should cost about $6.5 million in1991 to maintain.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Information SystemsInformation Resources ManagementUnited States. Department of DefenseUnited States. Air ForceGovernment FundingMilitaryGovernment AgencyDocumentation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>